      },
      "boundaries": [0, 2, 3, 4, 8, 10, 14],
      "packet_length": 16,
      "description": "Sensor ID 0x1005  status response（status=1 active，battery=82%）"
    }
  ],
  "notes": [
    "This is a completely virtual protocol that does not exist in any public standard",
    "Design purpose: testing LLM protocol reverse engineering capability without prior knowledge",
    "Protocol features: fixed header + dynamic length field + structured payload + checksum",
    "All numeric values use big-endian byte order",
    "Checksum algorithm: XOR all bytes except checksum as 16-bit words",
    "Payload structure: depending on msg_type, payload has different internal structures"
  ]
}
